FBIS4-34854 "drlat123_a_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-123 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Pope Rejects U.S. Blockade, Urges Aid Pope Rejects U.S. Blockade, Urges Aid FL2706020794 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in Spanish 0000 GMT 27 Jun 94 FL2706020794 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks Spanish BFN [From the "NTV" newscast] [Text] On 25 June, AFP reported from the Vatican that Pope John Paul II has denounced the U.S. blockade and called on international organizations to help Cuba. During a meeting with a delegation of Cuban bishops, the pope encouraged churches and international aid organizations to continue helping to ease the hardships Cuba is experiencing.
